[
    {
        "content": "<p>What is the rule to decide if to name a lemma <code>coe_add</code> or <code>add_coe</code>?</p>",
        "id": 241469591,
        "sender_full_name": "Nicol√≤ Cavalleri",
        "timestamp": 1622763054
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The naming guide says lemmas about <code>foo (bar x y) = ...</code> should be called <code>foo_bar</code></p>",
        "id": 241498352,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1622790677
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So <code>coe_add</code> would by that scheme be <code>coe (a + b) = ...</code> while <code>add_coe</code> would be <code>coe a + coe b = ...</code></p>",
        "id": 241498535,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1622790794
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/naming.html\">#naming</a></p>",
        "id": 241498551,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1622790806
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Although now that I look, I can't find that rule there...</p>",
        "id": 241498709,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1622790913
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the latter would be called <code>coe_add_coe</code></p>",
        "id": 241507444,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1622796925
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>add_coe would be something like <code>a + coe b = ...</code></p>",
        "id": 241507476,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1622796943
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but then what would <code>coe a + b</code> be? I would've assumed <code>coe_add</code></p>",
        "id": 241508305,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Rodriguez",
        "timestamp": 1622797499
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, the naming is ambiguous. This comes up for <code>(-a) * b = ...</code> vs <code>a * -b = ...</code> vs <code>-(a * b) = ...</code>, although the lemma names we choose for those are an awful mouthful</p>",
        "id": 241508439,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1622797580
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I bet <code>coe a + b</code> is much rarer in practice than examples where <code>a</code> and <code>b</code> have the same type</p>",
        "id": 241516506,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1622802503
    }
]